						<summary>

						<p>On a stone standing near the Rāmasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Chāḷukya: Sarvalokāśraya Vishṇuvardhana, 35th year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1017, Vishuvu Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 50 sheep to the god Mahēndrēśvara-Mahādēva of Elamañchi, for burning a perpetual lamp by Sūraya, son of Sūraparāju for the merit of his wife. Also refers to the gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">tūmus</hi> of land in Koṇḍupalli, which was a village in the enjoyment of the temple, for purpose of the lamps.</p>						

						</summary>
